      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bargain Flights</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jim Roby letter on September 3 travel article about low-cost European airlines adds Spanish carrier Air Europa (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: To your recent list of low-cost European airlines (''Bargain Flights Within Europe'' Sept. 3), may I add the Spanish carrier Air Europa?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: To your recent list of low-cost European airlines (''Bargain Flights Within Europe'' Sept. 3), may I add the Spanish carrier Air Europa?</p>
        <p>Last January I flew on Air Europa from Paris to Madrid and Bilbao for $140. To my amazement, on all three flights passengers were offered a choice of newspapers; drinks and real food (in one case a delicious jamon sandwich) were served at no charge; and hot towels and candies were distributed before landing.</p>
        <p>The Web site is www.air-europa .com.</p>
        <p>JIM ROBY  Provincetown, Mass.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
